This is a retrograde law that is sometimes referred to by members of women’s rights networks in Pakistan as Pakistan’s “One Child Policy”. In several provinces, it is common to see posters advertising government-run centers informing pregnant women who are unable/unwilling to care for their children about their compliance obligation to be sterilized.
